description:
All other things (service, menu, etc.) being equal, there are four benchmarks I use to grade a Starbucks:

(1) Floor layout/Number of tables;
(2) General probability of an available table;
(3) Availability/number of electrical sockets for laptops/cell phone chargers;
(4) Cleanliness of the bathroom.

The ladies bathroom here is consistently clean; there are plugs under the benches lining the left wall; usually there are tables to be had (only once out of many times was I SOL); the layout is not too cluttered; there's a greater than average number of chairs/tables at this Starbucks.

My #1 study starbucks in SOMA/financial district.
